generatorNotes:
MCP servers communicate over JSON-RPC stdio per the Model Context Protocol spec. agent-bober already has src/mcp/ for its own MCP server (existing); the new src/mcp/external-client.ts is the inverse — agent-bober as an MCP CLIENT consuming external servers.

Lifecycle:
```typescript
class ExternalMcpServer {
  async start(): Promise<void> {
    this.child = execa(this.config.mcpCommand, this.config.mcpArgs ?? [], { env: { ...process.env, ...this.config.mcpEnv }, stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'pipe'] });
    await this.handshake();
  }
  async listTools(): Promise<ToolDescriptor[]> { ... }
  async callTool(name: string, args: unknown): Promise<unknown> { ... }
  async stop(): Promise<void> { /* SIGTERM, wait 5s, SIGKILL */ }
}
```

Tool merge at subagent spawn:
```typescript
const coreTools = [Read, Bash, Grep, Glob];
const obsTools = await Promise.allSettled(
  config.observability.providers.map(p => startProvider(p).then(s => s.listTools()))
);
const mergedTools = [...coreTools, ...obsTools.flatMap((r, i) => r.status === 'fulfilled' ? r.value.map(t => ({ ...t, name: `obs__${config.observability.providers[i].name}__${t.name}` })) : (console.warn(`Provider ${config.observability.providers[i].name} failed: ${r.reason}`), []))];
```

Reference adapter docs: each file ~50-100 lines.
- logs.md: contract for a logs MCP. Required tools: query_logs(query, timeRange), get_log_context(logId). Example servers: Grafana Loki via mcp-grafana, Datadog via mcp-datadog (community).
- metrics.md: query_metric(name, timeRange, aggregation), list_metrics, get_metric_metadata.
- traces.md: query_traces(service, timeRange), get_trace(traceId).
- errors.md: query_errors(timeRange, severity), get_error_detail(errorId), get_error_breadcrumbs(errorId).
- README.md: how to add a new provider, namespace convention, security considerations.

Docs ship contract-only because shipping integrations creates maintenance burden agent-bober doesn't want and forces specific vendor choices on users.
